  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2511",
  "title": "Negative values unsupported in range slider",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nBug. Example: https://jsfiddle.net/8zzvL5y1/\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nAttributes with negative values do not show those negative values in the range slider. Additionally, explicitly setting a negative minimum doesn't seem to fix anything.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nI'd expect any positive or negative numbers to be supported.\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\n\r\nChrome (Mac) 61.0.3163.100\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\n\r\n- support negative values in facets\r\n- set range selection minimum appropriately\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nhttps://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@1/dist/instantsearch.min.css\r\n",
